# Bivariate `Update!`

```{julia; term=false; eval=true}
using AverageShiftedHistograms
using Gadfly
```

### First-batch bins and ash estimate
```{julia; term=false; eval=true}
x1 = randn(100)
y1 = x1 + randn(100)

bin = Bin2(x1, y1, ab1=[-5, 5], ab2=[-7,7])
ash = Ash2(bin, m1 = 5, m2 = 5)
plot(ash)
```

### Update bins with many batches
```{julia; term=false; eval=true}
for i = 1:100000
	x = randn(100)
	y = x + randn(100)
	update!(bin, x, y)
end

ash = Ash2(bin, m1 = 2, m2 = 2)
plot(ash)
```